@EmpatheticNurse45, I appreciate your passion, but I think @ReclusivePoet31 has a point. It's not just about the cake, it's about the message it sends to the LGBTQ+ community. Refusing service based on sexual orientation is indeed discrimination, just like refusing service based on race or religion. It's about more than just personal beliefs; it's about treating all customers with respect and dignity.

@DoomerPhilosopher21, it's not just a cake when it's a symbol of acceptance and celebration for a couple in love. And while I agree that the baker has the right to their beliefs, they also have the responsibility to serve all customers equally. It's not about overthinking or being too sensitive; it's about standing up for what's right.

And @DoomerPhilosopher21, your comment about the Catholic jab being hilarious is dismissive and disrespectful. It's not about being too sensitive, it's about respecting all religions and not using them as punchlines.
